# Platform-Specific Deltas

This rule covers ONLY what differs from web defaults. Spacing, color, typography, accessibility, and component anatomy come from `[00-design-principles.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/00-design-principles.mdc)`, `[10-tokens-and-scales.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/10-tokens-and-scales.mdc)`, and `[50-components.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/50-components.mdc)`. Do not duplicate them here.

For full canonical references see `[.mba-template/platforms/](mdc:.mba-template/platforms/)`.

---

## iOS / iPadOS

### Safe areas — non-negotiable
- Top: status bar + Dynamic Island / notch (44–59pt). Use `safe-area-inset-top`.
- Bottom: home indicator (34pt). Use `safe-area-inset-bottom`.
- Web: `viewport-fit=cover` + `padding: env(safe-area-inset-*)`.

### Native font
- SF Pro (UI), SF Pro Display (large titles), SF Mono (code), New York (serif).
- Web fallback: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont`.

### Dynamic Type
- Never use fixed `pt` sizes. Use `UIFont.preferredFont(forTextStyle:)` (SwiftUI: `.font(.body)`) or web `font: -apple-system-body`.

### Navigation
- Navigation bar: 44pt compact, 96pt with large title.
- Tab bar: 49pt, 2–5 tabs.
- Back: automatic + edge swipe gesture (don't override).

### Buttons (UIKit/SwiftUI variants)
- `.borderedProminent` (filled), `.bordered` (tinted), `.plain` (text). No outlined variant — that's Material.

### Touch targets
- Minimum 44pt × 44pt. Recommended 48pt.

### Sheets
- Detents: medium (half-screen), large (full). Use `.presentationDetents([.medium, .large])` in SwiftUI.

### Test
- VoiceOver (Settings → Accessibility → VoiceOver), Reduce Motion, both light and dark mode.

---

## Android

### Material Design 3 (M3)
- Use `MaterialTheme` (Compose) or `Material3` themes (XML).
- Dynamic color: derive palette from wallpaper via `dynamicLightColorScheme()` / `dynamicDarkColorScheme()`.
- Tonal palettes: 13 tones per color role.
- Elevation expressed via surface tinting, not just shadow.

### Native font
- Roboto (default) or Roboto Flex (variable). Code: Roboto Mono.

### Type scale (M3)
- Display, Headline, Title, Body, Label — each with Large / Medium / Small.
- Support system font scaling (don't disable `fontScale`).

### Navigation
- Top app bar: 64dp.
- Bottom navigation: 80dp, 3–5 destinations.
- Navigation drawer: 360dp standard.
- Navigation rail: 80dp (vertical, for tablets/foldables).

### Buttons (M3)
- `Filled`, `FilledTonal`, `Outlined`, `Text`, `Elevated`. FAB: Small 40dp / Medium 56dp / Large 96dp.

### Touch targets
- Minimum 48dp × 48dp. Spacing 8dp between adjacent targets.

### Test
- TalkBack, both light and dark themes, dynamic color enabled and disabled.

