## Desktop apps (Electron / Tauri)

### Window chrome
- Title bar: 32–40px (Windows), 22px (macOS — traffic lights).
- Custom title bar: define drag region (`-webkit-app-region: drag` on container, `no-drag` on interactive elements).
- Resize from all edges (default), or set min/max sizes.

### Layout chrome
- Menu bar: 28–32px (Windows native menu OR custom). On macOS, use the system menu bar via app menu.
- Toolbar: 40–48px.
- Sidebar: 240–280px, collapsible.
- Status bar: 24–28px.

### Keyboard shortcuts (must support)
| Action | macOS | Windows / Linux |
|--------|-------|-----------------|
| New | ⌘N | Ctrl+N |
| Open | ⌘O | Ctrl+O |
| Save | ⌘S | Ctrl+S |
| Close | ⌘W | Ctrl+W |
| Quit | ⌘Q | Ctrl+Q (Alt+F4) |
| Preferences | ⌘, | Ctrl+, |
| Find | ⌘F | Ctrl+F |
| Undo / Redo | ⌘Z / ⌘⇧Z | Ctrl+Z / Ctrl+Y |

### Click targets
- Minimum 24px × 24px (mouse-driven, denser than touch). Hover states are mandatory.

### Right-click
- Context menus expected for lists, text fields, content areas. Use native menu APIs (Tauri: `Menu`, Electron: `Menu.buildFromTemplate`).

### System theme
- Honor `prefers-color-scheme`. On Tauri, listen to `tauri::api::os::os_type` and theme events. On Electron, `nativeTheme.shouldUseDarkColors`.

