## Cross-platform decision tree

When the same product targets multiple platforms:

1. **Shared:** spacing scale, semantic color tokens, typography hierarchy, accessibility floor — all from core rules.
2. **Diverge:**
   - Navigation: bottom tabs (iOS), bottom nav (Android), sidebar (desktop), top nav (web).
   - Fonts: SF Pro (iOS), Roboto (Android), system stack (desktop/web).
   - Components: filled/bordered/plain (iOS), filled/tonal/outlined/text/elevated (Android M3), shadcn-style (web).
   - Gestures: edge swipe back (iOS), system gesture nav (Android), keyboard + mouse (desktop).

3. **Never:** force one design across all platforms. A web-styled iOS app feels broken. A Material Android app on iOS feels foreign.

